message.entry: Turning the mpm feature on or off from within MATLAB is not permitted. Please restart MATLAB using matlab -mpm or -nompm.
This command is not supported when the mpm feature is not enabled. Start MATLAB with the -mpm command line switch.
Comparison between {0} and {1} is not supported.
Turning the packages feature on or off from within MATLAB is not permitted. Please restart MATLAB using matlab -packages or -nopackages.

Unable to get previously installed packages because the database has been corrupted. The current session started with no package installed. You can still use package features normally, but no package installation configuration will be saved after closing the MATLAB.\n\nTo address this issue, please manually delete the file 'packages.mlsettings' under the preferences folder (prefdir). This will erase your previous package installation configuration.
Installing MPM packages is not supported by MATLAB Compiler. Remove functions that install/uninstall packages.
